Below is a worked‐through example of how one can interpret and build the shown “arched tower” from the block set.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIPTION OF THE TARGET STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Total Block Count: 8 pieces  
• Number of “Layers”: 4 main horizontal levels  
  – Layer 1 (the base):  
    ◦ Two red triangular wedges on the far left and right  
    ◦ A circular “tunnel”/arch in the center (actually made from two matching halves)  
  – Layer 2 (middle block):  
    ◦ One red rectangular/cubic block sitting atop the arch  
  – Layer 3 (the yellow domes):  
    ◦ Two yellow half‐cylinders side‐by‐side along the front/top edge  
  – Layer 4 (the roof):  
    ◦ One red triangular wedge centered on top  

Spatially, the two triangular wedges at the bottom flank a circular opening. Above that sits the rectangular red block; on its front edge are two half‐cylinders in yellow. Lastly, a single red wedge caps the top.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING THE CORRECT DICTIONARY BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
To match both shape and orientation exactly (no extra rotation allowed), the following blocks must be chosen from the dictionary:

• (4) Red half‐arch (left half)  
• (5) Red half‐arch (right half)  
  – Together these form the circular “tunnel” in the center.  
• (13) Red triangular wedge (oriented to fit the left base)  
• (16) Red triangular wedge (mirrored orientation for the right base)  
• (11) Red rectangular/cubic block for the center/top layer  
• (6)  Yellow half‐cylinder (left orientation)  
• (7)  Yellow half‐cylinder (right orientation)  
• (12) Red triangular wedge for the roof  

Hence the required block‐index list is:  
[4, 5, 11, 12, 13, 16, 6, 7]

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is a simple top‐to‐bottom sequence you might use:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 13  // Left bottom wedge
  Step2: Move block with index 16  // Right bottom wedge
  Step3: Move block with index 4   // Left half of the central arch
  Step4: Move block with index 5   // Right half of the central arch
  Step5: Move block with index 11  // Red rectangular block on top of arch
  Step6: Move block with index 6   // Left yellow half‐cylinder on the middle block
  Step7: Move block with index 7   // Right yellow half‐cylinder on the middle block
  Step8: Move block with index 12  // Red triangular wedge (roof)
}

This completes the structure exactly as shown in the target image.
